<center><b><font color="#1A1AFF"><font size=+3>Confidence Intervals for
SAGE Tags</font></font></b>
<br><b><font color="#1A1AFF"><font size=+3>(<i>CIST</i>)</font></font></b>
<p><b><font color="#1A1AFF">A WINDOWS PROGRAM FOR THE ANALYSIS OF GENE
EXPRESSION DATA GENERATED USING THE SERIAL ANALYSIS OF GENE EXPRESSION
TECHNIQUE</font></b></center>
<b><font color="#1A1AFF"></font></b>
<p><br><b></b>
<p><b>SYSTEM REQUIREMENTS</b>
<p>CIST is designed to work with any system running Windows 9x/NT.&nbsp;
Approximately 1 MB of hard-drive space is required for program files. Given
that most analyses are computationally involved, a Pentium II class CPU
or faster is highly recommended.
<p><b>DOWNLOADING AND INSTALLING CIST:</b>
<p>1) Download the self-extracting archive "cistzip.exe" <a href="CISTzip.exe">**Click
here to start downloading***</a>.
<br>File last updated 1 May 2000.
<p><b>Please be sure to <a href="mailto:Mark.Miller@usu.edu">send the
author an e-mail message</a> if you download this program.&nbsp; Please
specify that you have obtained CIST and include a return e-mail address
in the message.</b>
<p>2) Double-click the self-extracting archive to start the installation
procedure and follow the on-screen instructions.
